json server:
    json server is a light weight and easy to use node.js tool that can stimulate restful apis using json file as a data source
    ->basically used by front end developers
    ->basically used for testing
    ->can performe crud 
    crud
      create-read-update-delete
      http 


STEPS TO SETUP JSON SERVER:
  1->create seperate folder for the server
  2->create pakage.json -->config
    npm init -y
  3-->install json server library
       npm i json-server
       npm i json-server@0.17.4--version

  4->create .gitignore file outside
  5->create .json file to store data
  6->only file that runs in the server side (index.js)
  7->edit script tag
     in pakage .json file
  8->create server in index.js
       *import json server library
         const jsonServer =require('json-server')
         *create server using create method library



         3000(react run)
         5170(vite)
         4200(angular)


side effect:
   useEffect-used to handle side effects
   eg:api
    useEffect(()=>{

    },dependency)
    1:function
    2:dependency-optional
       ->no dependency-calls in every render
       ->empty array-call when component render into the browser
       ->[state,props]-call when the component render into the browser as well as the value of props or state change


